Moscow Vnukovo airport closes runway for repairs . Vnukovo airport closed one of its two runways on Monday for repair work until August 1 , a senior aiport official said . Nikolai Dubovitski , deputy head of Vnukovo airport , told Reuters that the landing and lighting system on the runway would be replaced with a more modern system . " At the airport there will be work as usual during these two months . . . without any flights postponed , " he said , adding that all airlines which use Vnukovo had been told about the runway ' s closure . Vnukovo is the second largest of four Moscow airports , and operates mostly domestic flights . It also operates some international scheduled and charter flights . - - Viktor Anoshkin , Moscow Newsroom , + 7095 941 8520 
